# Test Case Set — 521 — Remove Live Cancel/Update Buttons From Company Profile View

## Metadata
- Case ID: 521  
- Source Artifact: Jira Ticket 521 PDF — “Remove Live Cancel/Update Buttons From The Lower Right Corner Of The Company Profile Page View”  
- Agent Used: Test Case Generator  
- Test Author: Adam Musinski  
- Date Created: 2026-03-23  
- Scope: Company Profile page View and Edit modes, Cancel and Update button visibility, behavior, validation, data persistence, and role-based access.  
- Out of Scope: Backend data model changes, database integrity beyond UI-observable persistence, performance testing, and cross-browser UI styling differences not described in the ticket.

---

## Objective

Validate that the Company Profile page enforces correct UI behavior between View and Edit modes by ensuring Cancel and Update actions are only available in Edit mode, do not cause unintended data loss, trigger validation correctly, and preserve saved data. Validation focuses exclusively on observable UI behavior and user-facing outcomes.

---

## Preconditions

- System is deployed to a testable environment.
- Monitoring/observability tooling is enabled.
- User has access to the Company Profile feature with role-appropriate permissions.

---

## Assumptions & Constraints

- Users may trigger validation errors through invalid input, but no action should erase existing data.
- Functional behavior must match documented acceptance criteria only.
- Observability signals may lag behind UI behavior and are not user-visible.

---

## Acceptance Criteria (Derived)

| AC ID | Description |
|-----|-------------|
| AC-01 | Cancel and Update buttons are hidden and inaccessible in View mode. |
| AC-02 | Cancel and Update buttons are visible and enabled only in Edit mode. |
| AC-03 | No Update action can be triggered while in View mode. |
| AC-04 | Entering Edit mode preserves existing Company Profile data. |
| AC-05 | Clicking Update does not clear populated fields. |
| AC-06 | Validation does not show errors or erase data when inputs are valid. |
| AC-07 | Validation errors appear only for invalid or missing fields and do not erase other data. |
| AC-08 | Data persists after a successful Update. |
| AC-09 | Cancel discards unsaved changes and restores last saved data. |
| AC-10 | Users without edit rights cannot access Edit, Cancel, or Update actions. |
| AC-11 | Authorized roles can edit and save without data loss. |
| AC-12 | Cancel and Update buttons appear in a consistent location without duplication. |

